The paper discusses the use of pseudorandom generators in internet communication systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of chaotic iterations, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The statistical analysis of the proposed technique involves the use of standard criteria, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and network protocols (cs.NI).
